# ansible-lint starts at the `min` profile: it enforces the checks that catch REAL breakage
# (syntax-check, load/parse failures, internal errors) — complementing yamllint's YAML-validity pass.
#
# The roles don't yet follow ansible-lint's stricter *conventions* (role var-name prefixes, task
# naming, pipefail on shell pipes, explicit file modes — ~97 findings at the `basic` profile). Those
# are a cleanup backlog, not bugs. Ratchet this up over time: min -> basic -> moderate -> production,
# fixing findings as you go. Some (risky-shell-pipe, risky-file-permissions) are worth prioritizing.
profile: min
